static integer variable.
-----------------------

they retain there values between function calls.




static methods are called class methods.
because they r accesed wid class name and . dot operator
other methods are called by creating objects.

class STesting
{
	private static int counter;
	
	public static int getCounter()
	{
		return ++counter;
	}
	
}

we can call wid object but
this is not a right way to call any static method.


public class StaticTesting {

	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		
	System.out.println("Counter : " +  STesting.getCounter());	
		
		
	}
	
}



